TMicahT9 wrote a review Mar 2023
Metro Minneapolis-Saint Paul, Minnesota719 contributions
4 nights turned into 2 weeks
We thoroughly enjoyed our stay at Ala Carte. We initially booked a 4 nights stay but ended up extending it to two weeks. The location is perfect for long walks on the beach and exploring. The rooms are significantly larger than standard hotels, spotlessly clean, and very comfortable. We had stayed here in a vacation rental in the past and I have to say the quality and cleanliness of booking through the hotel is far superior. Breakfast is fresh with excellent and wide ranging selections. Best of all, the staff are very customer focused. We especially appreciated Bao, Ngoc, and Giang, the bellmen, who were always genuinely kind, helpful, and made us feel very welcomed. Highly recommended.
Date of stay: February 2023
Responded Mar 5, 2023
Dear, Greeting from √Ä La Carte Danang Beach! Thank you for patronizing √Ä La Carte, and taking time out to share your experience on Tripadvisor. All of us are delighted that we could ensure a comfortable stay during you visit. Thank you once again for your stay and your feedback and look forward to welcoming you back to √Ä La Carte Danang Beach. Have a nice day! √Ä La Carte Team
Patrick C wrote a review Feb 2023
Perth, Australia8 contributions
Perfect location Perfect property
We have just returned home to Perth from a stay in Da Nang. Thanks to the A La Carte staff and general comfort of this hotel made our visit to Vietnam so much more enjoyable. The only thing to be carefull of when booking are rooms with city view actually look out onto a building being constructed next door. Buffet breakfast a fantastic variety and choise for asian or western cuisine in a spacious and well set out restaurant.
